        "created_at": "2024-09-16T17:05:11.624Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hi, I’m trying desperately to recover some old messages and can’t tell which other posts may apply to my situation or not.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>I had an iphone 7 plus which I broke. The phone worked enough that for a while it was turning on and staying on long enough to attempt data transfers.</li>\n<li>I tried to move my signal messages through an account transfer to a new iphone. I believe I tried to transfer by a total data transfer from one phone to the next as well as doing the transfer through the signal app.</li>\n<li>I’m not sure why, but a transfer of my signal account <em>with messages</em> to the new iphone kept failing.</li>\n<li>I eventually chose to authorize a transfer of my signal account to the new iphone without transferring my messages. I believe that I authorized this transfer on the old iphone.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>I did not realize that this would cause me to lose all my messages permanently.</p>\n<p><strong>Does anyone know if it is possible to get old messages back by transferring my signal account back to an old device</strong> that had all my messages stored on it, <strong>or to get those messages from the broken phone by any other means?</strong></p>\n<p>Thank you in advance for your help, this is very important to me!</p>\n<p>(P.S. I’ve spent many hours trying to find the answer to this and also trying to recover the messages from an unlinked laptop, which resulted in a dead end. I’m not sure which rules apply to my situation and which do not just based on reading the documentation and it would probably be a huge effort to try to extract something from the broken phone, so I really need an expert opinion here!)</p>",
